May we all be as excited as Everleigh each time we visit Disney ❤️ Her face at the end meeting Mickey yesterday…I can’t 🥹🐭

Trying to pull myself together long enough to write this, my heart just hurts so much. Last week we said goodbye to our sweet, beautiful boy Ewok. He was the love of our lives. Words cannot express the sadness our family has been feeling. This is by far the most difficult time and the worst feeling in the whole world. He was our baby. He was the sweetest, most gentle and loving boy since the day he was born and I’ve always been so incredibly lucky to be his mama. The bond he shared with myself and my husband and with the girls is unmatched. The way he would play with the girls and give them a million kisses and rush to their side the moment one of them was hurt…that was how sweet and caring he was. He always had the world’s biggest heart. 

It’s not something I share about on here because it’s too hard for me to talk about and too close to my heart, but he’s had his share of health issues over the years and yet despite everything he’s been through, he’s always been so strong and such a happy boy. He loved life and his family so much and we loved him and will always love him more than anything. 
This has been a particularly difficult year for him in terms of health issues and yet he was so strong the whole way through. He truly amazed us all, including the vets and specialists that met him and worked so hard to save him. 

I want nothing more than to go back in time and kiss and hug him over and over. He was the most special boy in the world. I will love you forever my perfect boy. ❤️🐕
